The evidence with the title 'What's driving Africa's growth | McKinsey & Company ' says To be sure, Africa has benefited from the surge in commodity prices over the past decade . Oil rose from less than $20 a barrel in 1999 to more than $145 in 2008. Prices for minerals , grain, and other raw materials also soared on rising global demand . Yet the commodity boom explains only part of Africa's broader growth  ... 
